Post.create!([
  {title: "Revisiting Three EPs", body: "<p>While working on the new LP, tentatively called The Conjurer's Thread, I wanted to spruce up the old tracks that were sounding a bit flat and unfocused. I was also able to make a few changes to things that bothered me upon re-listen. As result, Hoarding Eleven has been re-leased as an EP, 'creatively' named Hoarding Sixteen, with many of the narrative bits replaced. The tracks were all sent to Alan Douches at West West Side for a proper mastering.</p>\r\n<p>The uncleared samples have made physically releasing this music practically impossible, so for now they remain digital only.</p>", main_image: "v1475671074/scagyl9iyhxzkpd0gpep.jpg", inline_image: nil, description: "Refreshed, Remastered and Still No Where to Go", overlay_bright: true, is_live: false, post_date: "2016-10-16 00:00:00"},
  {title: "Hoarding 17", body: "<p>The original Hoarding Eleven album contained a lot of soundtrack and audio collages. <em>Hoarding 17&nbsp;</em>pulls out the more self-contained songs to give them another look with new recording, mixes and mastering. This EP is available at bandcamp.com for the lowly price of $2.&nbsp;</p>", main_image: "v1492519916/sfby7zngx0dc26gwuurw.jpg", inline_image: nil, description: "New-ish EP coming 4/17/17", overlay_bright: false, is_live: false, post_date: "2017-04-11 00:00:00"},
  {title: "Benefit for The Transgender Law Center", body: "<p>This Friday, August 4th, all proceeds from sales on <a href=\"https://daily.bandcamp.com/2017/07/31/this-friday-stand-with-bandcamp-in-support-of-trans-rights/\" target=\"_blank\">Bandcamp</a> will go to benefit the <a href=\"https://transgenderlawcenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">The Transgender Law Center</a>. TLC works to ensure people can&nbsp;\"live safely, authentically, and free from discrimination regardless of their gender identity or expression.\" In addition,<a href=\"https://earthlyframes.bandcamp.com/\"> all Earthly Frames proceeds</a> will go to benefit TLC as well. Please consider shopping at Bandcamp or <a href=\"https://transgenderlawcenter.org/about/support-the-work-of-tlc\" target=\"_blank\">donate directly to TLC</a>.</p>", main_image: "v1501759499/wchxgj578plg1z8f8t9y.png", inline_image: nil, description: "8/4 100% of Bandcamp sales will go to TLC to help advocate for the transgender community.", overlay_bright: true, is_live: false, post_date: "2017-08-03 00:00:00"},
  {title: "A Doorbell For Finite Beings", body: "<p><a href=\"http://www.earthlyframes.com/videos/1\">Watch the video</a> for the first track off the upcoming album, <em>Light Reading</em>, coming in January 2019. <a title=\"Substream Magazine\" href=\"https://substreammagazine.com/2018/11/premiere-earthly-frames-doorbell-finite-beings/\">See it first on Substream Magazine.</a></p>", main_image: "image/upload/v1543448544/aah4p0y8m9dcv7fq7dw1.jpg", inline_image: nil, description: "New Music Video.", overlay_bright: true, is_live: true, post_date: "2018-11-28 00:00:00"},
  {title: "First Full Length", body: "<p>The Conjurer's Thread is the first full length LP by The Earthly frames. It's being released on vinyl and digital in the early summer of 2017. Track list includes:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>The Conjurer's Thread</li>\r\n<li>Everyday Sigils</li>\r\n<li>An Unfortunate Conflict of Evidence</li>\r\n<li>All Basty</li>\r\n<li>Strings of Bad Luck</li>\r\n<li>Star Filter</li>\r\n<li>RSI Labeling Act</li>\r\n<li>Abandoner</li>\r\n<li>Sitting at the Rainbow Table</li>\r\n<li>The Outer Loop.</li>\r\n</ol>", main_image: "image/upload/v1492521587/mxmhbyjkihtpvxvbeacw.png", inline_image: "image/upload/v1492521588/prqbbg4c16naxbnyicn2.jpg", description: "Announcing the Earthly Frames first full length album. Coming in the early summer of '17", overlay_bright: true, is_live: false, post_date: "2017-04-18 00:00:00"},
  {title: "She Waits for Yesterday Music Video", body: "<p>Watch the video for <strong>She Waits for Yesterday</strong> from&nbsp;<strong>Light Reading</strong> on <a href=\"http://www.ghostcultmag.com/exclusive-video-premiere-the-earthly-frames-she-waits-for-yesterday/\">Ghost Cult Magazine</a>!</p>", main_image: "image/upload/v1547157233/jztg3z4w3mnf4eecdyl9.jpg", inline_image: nil, description: "New Video Premiere on Ghost Cult Magazine", overlay_bright: false, is_live: true, post_date: "2019-01-10 00:00:00"},
  {title: "Your Team Ring Archive", body: "<p>My father found a box of old YTR tapes this past summer. I've gone through and cleaned them up as much as I could, but lo-fi, unfortunately seems like a understatement. You can find the entire collection of recordings from 1992-2005 under the Your Team Ring moniker <a href=\"../../../ytr\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Some of my experiences&nbsp;in listening to this stuff again:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"Michael's in the words, I'm in the chair\" in <em>Do I Hear the Air?</em>&nbsp;to \"In the big red arm chair nothing comes to mind\" from <em>Glasses on the Roof</em>. I'm trying to remember if there was some sort of a narrative going on there. Might be just a lazy rhyme.</li>\r\n<li>I was a bit scared of the person singing on <em>9 Ways</em> and <em>Rise and Shine.&nbsp;</em>I wanted to remember what building \"an igloo out of snakes and filth\" could possibly mean.</li>\r\n<li>Some of the tape flaking made the records a little more interesting.</li>\r\n<li>Richy Midnight! He's still one of my favorite collaborators of all time.</li>\r\n</ul>", main_image: "v1475234111/rjlrb1rqpayrfyql7nyq.png", inline_image: "v1475233491/g4u8qdbljxuqjqwhenv7.png", description: "1992-2005", overlay_bright: true, is_live: false, post_date: "2016-09-30 00:00:00"},
  {title: "New Solillians", body: "<p>I'm very excited to be a part of the new Solillians album, <em>Shin.&nbsp;</em>Neptune Sweet and I back up Ben and Sharon Malkin on this mystic-tinged space music. The album is dedicated and inspired by the late,great Leonard Nimoy - arguably the original Hebrewnaught.</p>\r\n<p>Solillians is also playing a few shows this Fall:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.petescandystore.com/calendar/#event|9pm-sollilians|4657\">Pete's Candy Store, Brooklyn, NY November 19, 2016 @ 9:00 pm</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;w/&nbsp;<a href=\"http://landingsite.net/\">Landing</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.petescandystore.com/calendar/#event|9pm-sollilians|4657\">Cafe Nine, New Haven, CT December 3, 2016 @ 9:00pm</a> - w/&nbsp;<a href=\"http://landingsite.net/\">Landing</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>", main_image: "v1474979456/yslfsrxvuabr6sptubsw.jpg", inline_image: "v1474979456/rvuwsc18tgfsn7oinqj8.jpg", description: "Our thoughts to your thoughts", overlay_bright: true, is_live: false, post_date: "2016-10-13 00:00:00"},
  {title: "Ruine", body: "<i>Ruine</i> is a ten-song LP recorded in 2019 and early 2020. It was finished right before the COVID outbreak and shelved due to a lack of funds, etc. It, of course, has a concept (oh boy here we go again) this time about the nature of memory and what gets filled in the blanks when it erodes. There's a couple of songs about misspent youth, another few about vanishing places, and the obligatory weirdo sci-fi stuff. I hope to get it out to you when I can.", main_image: "image/upload/v1584366278/jlhf8eiwxs7uu6jnjxiv.jpg", inline_image: nil, description: "A new LP", overlay_bright: false, is_live: true, post_date: "2020-04-20 00:00:00"},
  {title: "New LP coming January 2019", body: "<p>In&nbsp;January of 2019, The Earthly Frames will release a second LP entitled \"Light Reading.\" Each song on the record is a strange little world emanating&nbsp;from an imagined book. With titles such as <em>A Doorbell for Finite Beings</em> and <em>The Architectural Mnemonics of M. </em>Nodisks, \"Light Reading\" is anything but, and we are left wondering what happens to a book too obtuse to be read, too obscure to be remembered. As they say, knowledge is the power. Fight the power.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>", main_image: "v1537440030/a4rm61x5wclk6vwy1ysf.jpg", inline_image: "v1537440030/ftnloqalmtjaialv8cob.jpg", description: "Announcing \"Light Reading\"", overlay_bright: true, is_live: false, post_date: "2018-09-20 00:00:00"},
  {title: "I Heart Noise Mini Fest", body: "<a href=\"https://ihrtn.net/watch-ihn-mini-fest-5-1/\">Watch</a> the I Heart Noise mini, streaming festival featuring Solillians comrades, So 'Lil, Electric Djinn, and Magoo, as well as Wolfbear, Skyjelly, and Matt DeMello. The COVID-themed \"Feel Better Soon\" performed in the video will be heading your way in the next week or so.", main_image: "image/upload/v1588765091/ca4wihqbhxahwb8wexi4.jpg", inline_image: nil, description: "Remote Streams", overlay_bright: true, is_live: true, post_date: "2020-05-05 00:00:00"}
])
